                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1035">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/428: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-22T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 22, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 22—12:14 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>99. Shanghai’s 1176, December 18, 10 a.m. Gage, Secretary of British Embassy, has
                    several times lately inquired whether I had been instructed to join in
                    representations to the Minister of Finance. I replied each time that I had
                    received no reply to my telegram No. 75, December 17, 2 p.m. to the Department
                    and was without instructions. This morning he telephoned that pursuant to
                    instructions just received he intended to make representation to the Minister of
                    Finance before noon even without similar action by other Missions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
